00:00:04.820 --> 00:00:07.230 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.230 --> 00:00:09.925 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.925 --> 00:00:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>>SEAN STONE:
These are the times

00:00:11.300 --> 00:00:12.467 align:middle line:90%
that we've been waiting for.

00:00:12.467 --> 00:00:14.480 align:middle line:84%
These are the times of
great transformation.

00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:16.850 align:middle line:84%
The hidden truths that
have been kept from humans

00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:18.380 align:middle line:84%
are beginning to
reveal themselves.

00:00:18.380 --> 00:00:20.060 align:middle line:84%
We know there are
people that are trying

00:00:20.060 --> 00:00:21.470 align:middle line:90%
to control other human beings.

00:00:21.470 --> 00:00:22.190 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE NOORY: No question.

00:00:22.190 --> 00:00:23.960 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: I'm not here to
indoctrinate anyone and tell

00:00:23.960 --> 00:00:25.040 align:middle line:90%
them how to think.

00:00:25.040 --> 00:00:27.050 align:middle line:84%
All I want them to do is stop
listening to the mainstream

00:00:27.050 --> 00:00:27.920 align:middle line:90%
media narrative.

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:31.040 align:middle line:84%
Because every person has the
right and the power to see

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:33.060 align:middle line:90%
the reality for themselves.

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:35.930 align:middle line:84%
We have to step into
our inner intuition.

00:00:35.930 --> 00:00:37.740 align:middle line:84%
Can I trust myself
to become the leader?

00:00:37.740 --> 00:00:40.560 align:middle line:84%
And that is what this age
that we're approaching now

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:41.360 align:middle line:90%
is really about.

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:46.280 align:middle line:90%


00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:47.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:47.780 --> 00:00:48.920 align:middle line:90%
Sean Stone is with us.

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:51.380 align:middle line:10%
He's the host of Gaia's
series, "Buzzsaw."

00:00:51.380 --> 00:00:55.010 align:middle line:10%
He's also a filmmaker, author,
actor, poet, and above all,

00:00:55.010 --> 00:00:57.860 align:middle line:10%
truth seeker and
spiritual activist.

00:00:57.860 --> 00:00:59.432 align:middle line:84%
Sean, welcome to
"Beyond Belief."

00:00:59.432 --> 00:01:01.640 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: It's a pleasure to
be here with you, George.

00:01:01.640 --> 00:01:03.057 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell me
about your works.

00:01:03.057 --> 00:01:04.970 align:middle line:90%
You've got a book on poetry out.

00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:06.980 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: I've got, well
not on poetry hopefully.

00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:10.350 align:middle line:10%
It's a book of poems called
"The Ephemeral Shades of Time,"

00:01:10.350 --> 00:01:13.250 align:middle line:10%
and it's a collection of
poems that I've written really

00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:14.150 align:middle line:10%
since high school.

00:01:14.150 --> 00:01:17.445 align:middle line:10%
I would say it's a coming of age
of the fantasy act, as we say,

00:01:17.445 --> 00:01:19.320 align:middle line:10%
the end of the 20th
century, at the beginning

00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:20.153 align:middle line:10%
of the 21st century.

00:01:20.153 --> 00:01:24.030 align:middle line:84%
So the poetry that was
in my soul before 9/11,

00:01:24.030 --> 00:01:26.810 align:middle line:84%
through that time period, the
darkness that I think we all

00:01:26.810 --> 00:01:28.737 align:middle line:90%
felt in that post 9/11 era.

00:01:28.737 --> 00:01:29.570 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:01:29.570 --> 00:01:30.830 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: The 2000s.

00:01:30.830 --> 00:01:33.590 align:middle line:84%
And so it's basically of
a young man's reflections

00:01:33.590 --> 00:01:36.390 align:middle line:84%
on his reality, on
love, and the world.

00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:38.390 align:middle line:84%
I was traveling at
a young age going

00:01:38.390 --> 00:01:42.320 align:middle line:84%
to refugee camps in
places like Sudan

00:01:42.320 --> 00:01:44.660 align:middle line:84%
and in Kenya and
Ethiopia and Somalia

00:01:44.660 --> 00:01:46.460 align:middle line:84%
and reflecting on
these journeys.

00:01:46.460 --> 00:01:49.250 align:middle line:84%
So it comes from
a place of soul.

00:01:49.250 --> 00:01:52.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's a deep part of
you that I did not see before.

00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:53.210 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Really?

00:01:53.210 --> 00:01:53.525 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:01:53.525 --> 00:01:55.155 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: I'm shallow
on the surface.

00:01:55.155 --> 00:01:56.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Not shallow,
but I just didn't

00:01:56.780 --> 00:01:59.300 align:middle line:84%
know that you were into
that aspect of life

00:01:59.300 --> 00:02:00.487 align:middle line:90%
and spirituality.

00:02:00.487 --> 00:02:01.820 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Absolutely, absolutely.

00:02:01.820 --> 00:02:05.000 align:middle line:84%
What else is there in life
except to hopefully share

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:08.330 align:middle line:84%
our souls in different
capacity through our search,

00:02:08.330 --> 00:02:11.000 align:middle line:84%
our quest for knowledge if
we're not looking for the deeper

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:15.530 align:middle line:84%
truths then we get lost in the
maze of the labyrinth I call

00:02:15.530 --> 00:02:18.290 align:middle line:84%
it, of mind, the
labyrinth of politics

00:02:18.290 --> 00:02:21.470 align:middle line:84%
and the momentary
expectations and desires.

00:02:21.470 --> 00:02:23.900 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's new
with Sean Stone?

00:02:23.900 --> 00:02:24.810 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Surviving.

00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:27.140 align:middle line:90%
I think that's the basis of it.

00:02:27.140 --> 00:02:29.100 align:middle line:84%
We're all surviving a
very difficult time.

00:02:29.100 --> 00:02:31.950 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time, I would
say that in a deeper level,

00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:33.950 align:middle line:84%
these are the times that
we've been waiting for.

00:02:33.950 --> 00:02:36.260 align:middle line:84%
These are the times of
great transformation.

00:02:36.260 --> 00:02:37.940 align:middle line:90%
The Great Awakening, so-called.

00:02:37.940 --> 00:02:40.490 align:middle line:84%
It's to me, it
resonates very deeply

00:02:40.490 --> 00:02:42.650 align:middle line:84%
with what people like
myself and you have been

00:02:42.650 --> 00:02:44.060 align:middle line:90%
talking about for a long time.

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:46.550 align:middle line:84%
The deeper truths,
the hidden truths

00:02:46.550 --> 00:02:48.588 align:middle line:84%
that have been kept
from humans are

00:02:48.588 --> 00:02:49.880 align:middle line:90%
beginning to reveal themselves.

00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:51.710 align:middle line:84%
I think more and more
people are realizing

00:02:51.710 --> 00:02:54.420 align:middle line:84%
that there's a lot more
going on behind the scenes.

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:56.060 align:middle line:84%
And so this is
the time basically

00:02:56.060 --> 00:02:59.690 align:middle line:84%
for us to do what we've
been trained to do.

00:02:59.690 --> 00:03:03.620 align:middle line:84%
We've been trained by our
knowledge, by our education,

00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:05.538 align:middle line:84%
by the hosting and
the questioning

00:03:05.538 --> 00:03:07.580 align:middle line:84%
and the research that
we've done over these years

00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:09.160 align:middle line:84%
to help guide people
in these times.

00:03:09.160 --> 00:03:09.890 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I feel.

00:03:09.890 --> 00:03:11.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We're
giving them a vehicle

00:03:11.390 --> 00:03:15.170 align:middle line:84%
to kind of escape what's
going on in life right now.

00:03:15.170 --> 00:03:17.300 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Escape, but
at a deeper level,

00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:19.010 align:middle line:84%
to actually really
witness it perhaps.

00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:20.750 align:middle line:84%
To go, see, I think
that we're all

00:03:20.750 --> 00:03:24.620 align:middle line:84%
facing modalities of
control and whether or not

00:03:24.620 --> 00:03:26.570 align:middle line:84%
we agree with the
modalities of control.

00:03:26.570 --> 00:03:27.950 align:middle line:84%
In the grand scheme
of things, we

00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:30.680 align:middle line:84%
have beings that want
to control other humans.

00:03:30.680 --> 00:03:32.030 align:middle line:90%
We talked about aliens.

00:03:32.030 --> 00:03:34.040 align:middle line:84%
We can talk about the power
structure, the political power

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:34.840 align:middle line:90%
structure.

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:37.820 align:middle line:84%
But in our reality, the question
is, who controls your reality?

00:03:37.820 --> 00:03:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And I think at a deeper level,
we're realizing we have to be.

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:44.930 align:middle line:84%
I am sovereign over
myself in my reality.

00:03:44.930 --> 00:03:47.090 align:middle line:84%
That's where I think
we are each confronting

00:03:47.090 --> 00:03:51.390 align:middle line:84%
this moment of saying, do I
trust that I can take control,

00:03:51.390 --> 00:03:52.790 align:middle line:84%
so I can step into
my sovereignty

00:03:52.790 --> 00:03:54.770 align:middle line:84%
and stop looking
to the leadership,

00:03:54.770 --> 00:03:57.530 align:middle line:84%
whether it be spiritual,
scientific, political, to tell

00:03:57.530 --> 00:03:58.490 align:middle line:90%
me what to do.

00:03:58.490 --> 00:04:00.530 align:middle line:84%
Can I trust myself
to become the leader?

00:04:00.530 --> 00:04:03.380 align:middle line:84%
And that is what this age
that we're approaching now

00:04:03.380 --> 00:04:04.550 align:middle line:90%
is really about.

00:04:04.550 --> 00:04:06.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You are the
son of a director I

00:04:06.260 --> 00:04:08.780 align:middle line:90%
admire, Oliver Stone.

00:04:08.780 --> 00:04:12.200 align:middle line:84%
Growing up with
Oliver as your dad,

00:04:12.200 --> 00:04:14.570 align:middle line:84%
did he teach you some of
these spiritual aspects?

00:04:14.570 --> 00:04:16.250 align:middle line:84%
Where did this
come from for you?

00:04:16.250 --> 00:04:19.022 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Yes, it came from,
to a certain degree, from him.

00:04:19.022 --> 00:04:19.980 align:middle line:90%
From my mother as well.

00:04:19.980 --> 00:04:22.287 align:middle line:84%
She also took me to self
realization fellowship.

00:04:22.287 --> 00:04:23.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, really?

00:04:23.120 --> 00:04:24.200 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Which
practiced meditation.

00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:25.910 align:middle line:84%
But it was a place
that respected

00:04:25.910 --> 00:04:27.620 align:middle line:90%
and integrated all religions.

00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:28.880 align:middle line:90%
It was created by Yogananda.

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:31.160 align:middle line:84%
So the idea was, you
studied from the Koran,

00:04:31.160 --> 00:04:33.500 align:middle line:84%
as you study from the Torah,
as you study from the New

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:34.860 align:middle line:90%
Testament or from Buddhism.

00:04:34.860 --> 00:04:37.910 align:middle line:84%
So both my parents were
open-minded in that regard

00:04:37.910 --> 00:04:41.120 align:middle line:84%
and very fluid when it
came to spiritual practice.

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:42.590 align:middle line:90%
They were never dogmatic.

00:04:42.590 --> 00:04:46.130 align:middle line:84%
So that young age, I was
exposed to spiritual teachings

00:04:46.130 --> 00:04:49.460 align:middle line:84%
and I started integrating
meditation into my worldview.

00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:52.160 align:middle line:84%
My father took me to places
like India, Nepal and Tibet

00:04:52.160 --> 00:04:53.270 align:middle line:90%
when I was 10 years old.

00:04:53.270 --> 00:04:53.510 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Fascinating.

00:04:53.510 --> 00:04:56.013 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: He taught me about
the third eye and these things

00:04:56.013 --> 00:04:57.680 align:middle line:84%
they really were
difficult, because when

00:04:57.680 --> 00:05:00.200 align:middle line:84%
you're a young man from the
West and you're 10 years old

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:03.278 align:middle line:84%
and you're impatient and you're
spoiled and you want your toys

00:05:03.278 --> 00:05:04.820 align:middle line:84%
and you want immediate
gratification,

00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:06.737 align:middle line:84%
it's very difficult to
understand that there's

00:05:06.737 --> 00:05:10.650 align:middle line:84%
a deeper patience that we have
to learn to surrender ourselves

00:05:10.650 --> 00:05:11.450 align:middle line:90%
to again.

00:05:11.450 --> 00:05:13.662 align:middle line:84%
There's what, some
divine power that

00:05:13.662 --> 00:05:15.620 align:middle line:84%
seems to be working
through creation to give us

00:05:15.620 --> 00:05:17.048 align:middle line:90%
this magic that we call life.

00:05:17.048 --> 00:05:18.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: At that
young age, was there

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:20.870 align:middle line:84%
anything that scared you
when you were confronted

00:05:20.870 --> 00:05:22.335 align:middle line:90%
by all these things?

00:05:22.335 --> 00:05:23.210 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Many things.

00:05:23.210 --> 00:05:26.210 align:middle line:84%
I think death is the fundamental
fear that we all face.

00:05:26.210 --> 00:05:27.710 align:middle line:90%
Our fundamental fears are--

00:05:27.710 --> 00:05:28.543 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: At any age.

00:05:28.543 --> 00:05:32.240 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: --Scarcity, scarcity,
and lack, feel of lack,

00:05:32.240 --> 00:05:33.720 align:middle line:90%
death is that ultimate lack.

00:05:33.720 --> 00:05:34.580 align:middle line:90%
You lack life.

00:05:34.580 --> 00:05:37.070 align:middle line:84%
So when we are afraid of death,
if we don't confront death,

00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:39.650 align:middle line:84%
in my teenage years, you
ask about the poetry.

00:05:39.650 --> 00:05:44.120 align:middle line:84%
Very much the poetry was
in the Jim Morrison sense,

00:05:44.120 --> 00:05:46.330 align:middle line:84%
a fascination with death,
a romanticization of death

00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:47.130 align:middle line:90%
perhaps.

00:05:47.130 --> 00:05:49.830 align:middle line:84%
But it was like I
had to look at death

00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:53.670 align:middle line:84%
and say, you are
inevitable, death.

00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:54.960 align:middle line:90%
What happens thereafter?

00:05:54.960 --> 00:05:58.140 align:middle line:84%
And when you go to that place,
and in that case for me,

00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:00.630 align:middle line:84%
it was going to that place
through some journeys.

00:06:00.630 --> 00:06:03.660 align:middle line:84%
I did a film called "Greystone
Park" about exploring a haunted

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:06.690 align:middle line:84%
mental hospital and
experiencing entities

00:06:06.690 --> 00:06:09.360 align:middle line:84%
I felt demonic that were
from a different dimension.

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:11.110 align:middle line:84%
Realizing that death
is not the end.

00:06:11.110 --> 00:06:13.290 align:middle line:84%
And when you know
it in your soul

00:06:13.290 --> 00:06:15.570 align:middle line:84%
that death is not
the end of living,

00:06:15.570 --> 00:06:16.620 align:middle line:84%
your soul will continue
the energy that you are.

00:06:16.620 --> 00:06:17.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's a transition,
that's all it is.

00:06:17.730 --> 00:06:19.272 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: The
transition, then there's

00:06:19.272 --> 00:06:20.290 align:middle line:90%
nothing to fear anymore.

00:06:20.290 --> 00:06:23.400 align:middle line:84%
All that really matters is what
you do with your soul energy

00:06:23.400 --> 00:06:24.750 align:middle line:90%
through this incarnation.

00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:26.583 align:middle line:84%
Because this is not the
beginning or the end

00:06:26.583 --> 00:06:27.510 align:middle line:90%
of who we really are.

00:06:27.510 --> 00:06:30.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Your book on poems is
called "The Ephemeral Shades

00:06:30.870 --> 00:06:32.100 align:middle line:90%
of Time" book.

00:06:32.100 --> 00:06:32.420 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yes.

00:06:32.420 --> 00:06:34.212 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's an amazing
book, and how many

00:06:34.212 --> 00:06:35.670 align:middle line:90%
poems do you have in there?

00:06:35.670 --> 00:06:37.080 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: It's about 100 pages.

00:06:37.080 --> 00:06:38.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I'll get
a million emails

00:06:38.520 --> 00:06:40.440 align:middle line:84%
if I don't play
one of your poems.

00:06:40.440 --> 00:06:42.474 align:middle line:90%
So let's take a look.

00:06:42.474 --> 00:06:43.860 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:06:43.860 --> 00:06:46.620 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Imagine a world
where hugs are greetings,

00:06:46.620 --> 00:06:50.340 align:middle line:84%
where words are honored because
we are genuinely happy to share

00:06:50.340 --> 00:06:52.660 align:middle line:90%
this world with each other.

00:06:52.660 --> 00:06:55.350 align:middle line:10%
Imagine a world where contracts
are expansions and agreements

00:06:55.350 --> 00:06:59.010 align:middle line:10%
are oral, because goods are
transacted between friends

00:06:59.010 --> 00:07:01.470 align:middle line:10%
until all share in the wealth.

00:07:01.470 --> 00:07:03.840 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a world where you're
not seen as a commodity,

00:07:03.840 --> 00:07:07.090 align:middle line:84%
because millions won't follow
soulless posers ignoring

00:07:07.090 --> 00:07:11.497 align:middle line:84%
the cues of social engineers,
for we are all creators.

00:07:11.497 --> 00:07:13.080 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a world where
people do what's

00:07:13.080 --> 00:07:15.480 align:middle line:84%
right by trusting
their intuition,

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:19.470 align:middle line:84%
no matter what their leaders
and laws tell them to.

00:07:19.470 --> 00:07:23.460 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a world where
the sickness in our souls

00:07:23.460 --> 00:07:28.320 align:middle line:84%
is treated as carefully as
a doctor working in the ER,

00:07:28.320 --> 00:07:32.700 align:middle line:84%
knowing that healing
only happens inside.

00:07:32.700 --> 00:07:35.110 align:middle line:10%
Imagine a world
where feelings are

00:07:35.110 --> 00:07:39.970 align:middle line:10%
valued enough to be expressed
instead of scoffed at,

00:07:39.970 --> 00:07:45.430 align:middle line:10%
because in the eyes of the young
is the heart of the mature.

00:07:45.430 --> 00:07:48.610 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a world where
imagination is honored

00:07:48.610 --> 00:07:51.250 align:middle line:84%
and society looks
at its own shadows

00:07:51.250 --> 00:07:55.040 align:middle line:84%
rather than projecting
them out onto others.

00:07:55.040 --> 00:07:57.100 align:middle line:90%
We'd all be set free.

00:07:57.100 --> 00:08:00.160 align:middle line:84%
Imagine if we stopped trying
to force the world the way

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:04.510 align:middle line:84%
we want it to be, and start
to love our life just the way

00:08:04.510 --> 00:08:06.480 align:middle line:90%
it is.

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:10.760 align:middle line:84%
Imagine if every child were
told that they are enough.

00:08:10.760 --> 00:08:16.320 align:middle line:84%
Instead of competing for more,
we'd make room for everyone.

00:08:16.320 --> 00:08:19.440 align:middle line:84%
Imagine a world where you have
nothing to prove, to breathe

00:08:19.440 --> 00:08:23.280 align:middle line:84%
is the miracle, to people
smile at your sight,

00:08:23.280 --> 00:08:29.540 align:middle line:84%
to know you are welcome
and thanks for being here.

00:08:29.540 --> 00:08:31.418 align:middle line:90%
