00:25:30.090 --> 00:25:31.600 align:middle line:90%
the last time we got together.

00:25:31.600 --> 00:25:32.400 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yes.

00:25:32.400 --> 00:25:34.800 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're
changing quickly.

00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:37.755 align:middle line:90%
What's fueling that?

00:25:37.755 --> 00:25:39.820 align:middle line:84%
The events of the
past few years?

00:25:39.820 --> 00:25:40.620 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yes.

00:25:40.620 --> 00:25:43.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my growth, I'm
maturing, you know, I'm

00:25:43.200 --> 00:25:45.660 align:middle line:84%
in a partnership
with my partner,

00:25:45.660 --> 00:25:48.690 align:middle line:84%
Kaya teaches breathwork,
which I advocate for people

00:25:48.690 --> 00:25:49.965 align:middle line:90%
because breathwork is a--

00:25:49.965 --> 00:25:51.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is that breathing?

00:25:51.090 --> 00:25:52.465 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: It's a
type of breathing

00:25:52.465 --> 00:25:54.830 align:middle line:84%
that activates you could
say altered states.

00:25:54.830 --> 00:25:56.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Give me an example.

00:25:56.250 --> 00:25:57.870 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Well,
I'll tell you, she

00:25:57.870 --> 00:26:00.390 align:middle line:84%
teaches circular breathwork,
which basically is continuous

00:26:00.390 --> 00:26:00.960 align:middle line:90%
breathing.

00:26:00.960 --> 00:26:02.370 align:middle line:90%
And you do it for about an hour.

00:26:02.370 --> 00:26:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And you literally go
into an altered state,

00:26:05.040 --> 00:26:07.390 align:middle line:84%
because it's not to
say that you're, you

00:26:07.390 --> 00:26:09.005 align:middle line:84%
don't need drugs to
get to that place.

00:26:09.005 --> 00:26:10.380 align:middle line:84%
And meditation
can get you there,

00:26:10.380 --> 00:26:11.530 align:middle line:84%
but it takes a lot of
meditation to do it.

00:26:11.530 --> 00:26:12.900 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's much safer too.

00:26:12.900 --> 00:26:15.060 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: And you just do it with
yourself, with your own breath.

00:26:15.060 --> 00:26:16.320 align:middle line:84%
And you realize
the power, this is

00:26:16.320 --> 00:26:18.237 align:middle line:84%
what a lot of the yogis,
a lot of the ancient,

00:26:18.237 --> 00:26:20.850 align:middle line:84%
the Cathars, a lot of the
mystic schools, they always did

00:26:20.850 --> 00:26:21.650 align:middle line:90%
breathwork.

00:26:21.650 --> 00:26:23.550 align:middle line:84%
But people didn't
necessarily understand it.

00:26:23.550 --> 00:26:25.860 align:middle line:84%
They would say it was
like demonic or something.

00:26:25.860 --> 00:26:28.763 align:middle line:84%
They were consorting with demons
and like some of these Cathars

00:26:28.763 --> 00:26:31.180 align:middle line:84%
were persecuted by the church,
for example, the Catholics.

00:26:31.180 --> 00:26:32.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I've noticed
this, Sean, too,

00:26:32.370 --> 00:26:34.540 align:middle line:84%
which is interesting with
what you're talking about.

00:26:34.540 --> 00:26:35.340 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yeah.

00:26:35.340 --> 00:26:36.870 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: With
moments before you're

00:26:36.870 --> 00:26:40.740 align:middle line:84%
about to do something
big, whether it's

00:26:40.740 --> 00:26:43.920 align:middle line:84%
a kid at a baseball
game getting up to bat

00:26:43.920 --> 00:26:46.500 align:middle line:84%
or you've got a big
speech or something,

00:26:46.500 --> 00:26:48.284 align:middle line:90%
people always seem to go.

00:26:48.284 --> 00:26:49.676 align:middle line:90%
[INHALES]

00:26:49.676 --> 00:26:51.070 align:middle line:90%
[EXHALES]

00:26:51.070 --> 00:26:52.667 align:middle line:90%
And then they go and do it.

00:26:52.667 --> 00:26:54.750 align:middle line:84%
Is that a little bit of
what you're talking about?

00:26:54.750 --> 00:26:56.820 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Deep breath
is the beginning of it.

00:26:56.820 --> 00:26:59.490 align:middle line:84%
And then certainly whatever you
want to do with your breath,

00:26:59.490 --> 00:27:00.930 align:middle line:90%
it's yours.

00:27:00.930 --> 00:27:02.220 align:middle line:90%
You can do many practices.

00:27:02.220 --> 00:27:03.553 align:middle line:90%
That's the beauty of breathwork.

00:27:03.553 --> 00:27:06.300 align:middle line:84%
We don't realize the power if we
only tune in to our own breath.

00:27:06.300 --> 00:27:09.060 align:middle line:84%
And again, I've seen many yogis
talk about this over the years.

00:27:09.060 --> 00:27:12.180 align:middle line:84%
The power of many of their
feats that the yogis have

00:27:12.180 --> 00:27:15.240 align:middle line:84%
been described as magical,
mystical, often at times,

00:27:15.240 --> 00:27:16.800 align:middle line:84%
they just describe
it as literally

00:27:16.800 --> 00:27:20.700 align:middle line:84%
using breath to shift
their entire being,

00:27:20.700 --> 00:27:22.290 align:middle line:90%
their entire reality.

00:27:22.290 --> 00:27:24.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We are being
bombarded nowadays

00:27:24.420 --> 00:27:28.920 align:middle line:84%
with all kinds of things,
social network, fake news,

00:27:28.920 --> 00:27:31.860 align:middle line:84%
interpretations by
the cable networks.

00:27:31.860 --> 00:27:35.230 align:middle line:84%
How are we going
to handle all that?

00:27:35.230 --> 00:27:37.090 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Learning
to trust ourselves.

00:27:37.090 --> 00:27:40.990 align:middle line:84%
It's like we have a humanity
here for thousands of years,

00:27:40.990 --> 00:27:44.290 align:middle line:84%
I would say that has been
mentally put into servitude,

00:27:44.290 --> 00:27:48.340 align:middle line:84%
mentally put into the patterns
of believing the government

00:27:48.340 --> 00:27:51.550 align:middle line:84%
takes care of this, the doctor
does that, the scientist knows

00:27:51.550 --> 00:27:55.150 align:middle line:90%
this, religion knows that.

00:27:55.150 --> 00:27:58.660 align:middle line:84%
We have to step into
our inner intuition

00:27:58.660 --> 00:28:00.830 align:middle line:84%
knowing that I am sovereign
over my mind, body

00:28:00.830 --> 00:28:04.103 align:middle line:84%
and spirit, that I actually am
the creator of my own reality.

00:28:04.103 --> 00:28:05.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:28:05.020 --> 00:28:05.820 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Right?

00:28:05.820 --> 00:28:08.440 align:middle line:84%
And that I can then transact
in commerce with people.

00:28:08.440 --> 00:28:10.707 align:middle line:84%
So to me, the future
of commerce is

00:28:10.707 --> 00:28:12.290 align:middle line:84%
the harmony of
interests saying, well,

00:28:12.290 --> 00:28:13.930 align:middle line:84%
I can transact
with human beings.

00:28:13.930 --> 00:28:16.055 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to transact
with big corporations that

00:28:16.055 --> 00:28:18.700 align:middle line:84%
have no soul, no personality,
no face, they're just,

00:28:18.700 --> 00:28:20.200 align:middle line:84%
they're just there
to take my money.

00:28:20.200 --> 00:28:22.370 align:middle line:84%
I want to transact with
human beings and commerce

00:28:22.370 --> 00:28:26.020 align:middle line:84%
with human beings and
choose my reality.

00:28:26.020 --> 00:28:28.270 align:middle line:90%
That's where I see us going.

00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:32.710 align:middle line:84%
And so media overall has been
mass mind control, mass spell

00:28:32.710 --> 00:28:35.232 align:middle line:84%
casting, because they've
played upon fears.

00:28:35.232 --> 00:28:36.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Intentionally.

00:28:36.190 --> 00:28:37.840 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Intentionally, fears.

00:28:37.840 --> 00:28:40.570 align:middle line:84%
You look at the origins of
media before Mockingbird,

00:28:40.570 --> 00:28:43.390 align:middle line:84%
when the CIA was
buying journalists,

00:28:43.390 --> 00:28:45.550 align:middle line:84%
the origins of media
itself came out

00:28:45.550 --> 00:28:48.550 align:middle line:84%
of OSS, Office of
Strategic Services,

00:28:48.550 --> 00:28:50.550 align:middle line:90%
war propaganda In World War II.

00:28:50.550 --> 00:28:52.300 align:middle line:84%
A lot of the people
that were in the heads

00:28:52.300 --> 00:28:55.660 align:middle line:84%
of the various studios,
networks, the beginning,

00:28:55.660 --> 00:28:59.515 align:middle line:84%
had backgrounds in military
intelligence or overall you

00:28:59.515 --> 00:29:00.890 align:middle line:84%
mind, you could
say mind control.

00:29:00.890 --> 00:29:03.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Look how the
Nazis handled propaganda.

00:29:03.130 --> 00:29:03.550 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Precisely.

00:29:03.550 --> 00:29:05.425 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They had a
department that did that.

00:29:05.425 --> 00:29:06.980 align:middle line:90%
It was a Ministry of Propaganda.

00:29:06.980 --> 00:29:07.780 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Precisely.

00:29:07.780 --> 00:29:09.010 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they
knew how to handle it.

00:29:09.010 --> 00:29:09.810 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Precisely.

00:29:09.810 --> 00:29:13.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Social
media today is huge.

00:29:13.000 --> 00:29:16.120 align:middle line:90%
Good or bad for us?

00:29:16.120 --> 00:29:17.620 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Everything
is good and bad,

00:29:17.620 --> 00:29:19.240 align:middle line:84%
everything is
positive and negative.

00:29:19.240 --> 00:29:20.290 align:middle line:90%
It's what we do with it.

00:29:20.290 --> 00:29:22.000 align:middle line:84%
Social media, as
far as the way I

00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:26.590 align:middle line:84%
see these platforms
censoring people and content,

00:29:26.590 --> 00:29:27.400 align:middle line:90%
that's unhealthy.

00:29:27.400 --> 00:29:29.110 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that they
have the right to do that.

00:29:29.110 --> 00:29:29.920 align:middle line:90%
On the other hand--

00:29:29.920 --> 00:29:31.360 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's a
private enterprise.

00:29:31.360 --> 00:29:32.500 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: So it's a
private enterprise,

00:29:32.500 --> 00:29:34.708 align:middle line:84%
but they're getting certain
benefits from government.

00:29:34.708 --> 00:29:38.170 align:middle line:84%
And so this was a big deal when
it came to this Section 230

00:29:38.170 --> 00:29:41.230 align:middle line:84%
and the recent
NDAA Bill of 2021.

00:29:41.230 --> 00:29:42.743 align:middle line:84%
The point is, that
they should be,

00:29:42.743 --> 00:29:44.410 align:middle line:84%
if they're going to
be censoring people,

00:29:44.410 --> 00:29:46.360 align:middle line:84%
they should be considered
as any other media, a media

00:29:46.360 --> 00:29:47.160 align:middle line:90%
conglomerate.

00:29:47.160 --> 00:29:48.470 align:middle line:90%
"The New York Times," CNN.

00:29:48.470 --> 00:29:49.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:29:49.270 --> 00:29:50.830 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: They don't get any
benefits, because they're not

00:29:50.830 --> 00:29:51.702 align:middle line:90%
free platforms.

00:29:51.702 --> 00:29:54.160 align:middle line:84%
So if Twitter wants to censor,
they're not a free platform.

00:29:54.160 --> 00:29:56.050 align:middle line:84%
If Facebook wants to censor,
they're not a free platform

00:29:56.050 --> 00:29:56.630 align:middle line:90%
anymore.

00:29:56.630 --> 00:29:57.520 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Good point.

00:29:57.520 --> 00:29:59.810 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: So I think that
there's a great benefit

00:29:59.810 --> 00:30:00.610 align:middle line:90%
for social media.

00:30:00.610 --> 00:30:04.000 align:middle line:84%
Just like the internet, if we
as people, again, commerce,

00:30:04.000 --> 00:30:06.460 align:middle line:84%
and we create our own
platforms and hopefully don't

00:30:06.460 --> 00:30:08.540 align:middle line:84%
get censored from
the internet itself,

00:30:08.540 --> 00:30:10.790 align:middle line:84%
so that we can actually have
our own platforms to say,

00:30:10.790 --> 00:30:12.370 align:middle line:84%
OK, we don't want to
work on Facebook anymore,

00:30:12.370 --> 00:30:13.720 align:middle line:90%
let's create our own Facebook.

00:30:13.720 --> 00:30:16.060 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You interviewed
journalist David Seaman

00:30:16.060 --> 00:30:18.370 align:middle line:90%
on "Buzzsaw" about this.

00:30:18.370 --> 00:30:19.170 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:30:19.170 --> 00:30:21.420 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Do you think that
what we're going to see now

00:30:21.420 --> 00:30:24.320 align:middle line:84%
is that Facebook, Twitter
and these other platforms

00:30:24.320 --> 00:30:26.420 align:middle line:84%
are going to try to
work to basically censor

00:30:26.420 --> 00:30:27.710 align:middle line:90%
the alternative voices?

