00:30:33.500 --> 00:30:36.290 align:middle line:84%
Why would I use Facebook
if I know they're starting

00:30:36.290 --> 00:30:38.225 align:middle line:90%
to censor alternative views?

00:30:38.225 --> 00:30:40.850 align:middle line:84%
People used to log into Facebook
to see what their friends were

00:30:40.850 --> 00:30:43.710 align:middle line:84%
thinking and to see what the
non-mainstream people were

00:30:43.710 --> 00:30:44.510 align:middle line:90%
thinking.

00:30:44.510 --> 00:30:46.885 align:middle line:84%
At least some people do that,
that's the point of Twitter

00:30:46.885 --> 00:30:48.980 align:middle line:90%
is to get these different views.

00:30:48.980 --> 00:30:51.530 align:middle line:10%
And yeah, what I
had read, I don't

00:30:51.530 --> 00:30:54.440 align:middle line:10%
know how credible this is,
but Zuckerberg and Facebook

00:30:54.440 --> 00:30:57.440 align:middle line:10%
were considering using
Media Matters for America

00:30:57.440 --> 00:30:59.600 align:middle line:10%
as the third party
vetting source

00:30:59.600 --> 00:31:03.440 align:middle line:10%
for what is fake news or not,
which I take exception to that.

00:31:03.440 --> 00:31:05.390 align:middle line:84%
Because the founder
of Media Matters

00:31:05.390 --> 00:31:08.870 align:middle line:84%
is David Brock, a very
close Clinton insider.

00:31:08.870 --> 00:31:11.355 align:middle line:84%
This is not a claim that
anybody can push back against,

00:31:11.355 --> 00:31:12.480 align:middle line:90%
because everybody knows it.

00:31:12.480 --> 00:31:14.420 align:middle line:84%
He's very close to
the Clintons, and he's

00:31:14.420 --> 00:31:16.880 align:middle line:84%
very close to some of
the people involved

00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:19.100 align:middle line:84%
in some upcoming
political scandals.

00:31:19.100 --> 00:31:22.070 align:middle line:84%
So they're simply not
credible to judge something

00:31:22.070 --> 00:31:23.012 align:middle line:90%
in an unbiased way.

00:31:23.012 --> 00:31:25.220 align:middle line:84%
Why don't we, we don't want
that on the right either.

00:31:25.220 --> 00:31:27.270 align:middle line:84%
We don't want some
right wing think tank

00:31:27.270 --> 00:31:28.980 align:middle line:84%
to tell us what is
news and what is not,

00:31:28.980 --> 00:31:31.010 align:middle line:84%
so why would we want the
left wing version of that?

00:31:31.010 --> 00:31:32.120 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: You don't want
Steve Bannon's group

00:31:32.120 --> 00:31:33.530 align:middle line:84%
basically censoring
the news any more

00:31:33.530 --> 00:31:36.110 align:middle line:84%
than Brock, who is a super PAC
donor for the Democratic party.

00:31:36.110 --> 00:31:36.590 align:middle line:90%
>>SEAMAN: Exactly.

00:31:36.590 --> 00:31:38.570 align:middle line:84%
Why should fact-checking
be a political thing?

00:31:38.570 --> 00:31:39.080 align:middle line:90%
It shouldn't.

00:31:39.080 --> 00:31:39.350 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Exactly.

00:31:39.350 --> 00:31:40.580 align:middle line:90%
It should not be politicized.

00:31:40.580 --> 00:31:43.310 align:middle line:84%
And so I think
obviously, the key

00:31:43.310 --> 00:31:46.310 align:middle line:84%
is going to be
how do we survive.

00:31:46.310 --> 00:31:47.960 align:middle line:84%
Also even in this
administration,

00:31:47.960 --> 00:31:51.320 align:middle line:84%
we don't know what's going
to come as far as utilizing

00:31:51.320 --> 00:31:54.080 align:middle line:84%
censorship as a tool
basically to silence

00:31:54.080 --> 00:31:55.380 align:middle line:90%
the dissident voices.

00:31:55.380 --> 00:31:57.950 align:middle line:84%
But to me, it's like people
talk about how America

00:31:57.950 --> 00:32:01.310 align:middle line:84%
is more divided maybe since
going back to the Civil Rights

00:32:01.310 --> 00:32:03.980 align:middle line:84%
era, the Civil War, people are
talking about this very divided

00:32:03.980 --> 00:32:06.572 align:middle line:84%
climate as though
it's a bad thing.

00:32:06.572 --> 00:32:08.030 align:middle line:84%
Don't you agree
maybe actually this

00:32:08.030 --> 00:32:09.080 align:middle line:90%
is exactly what we do need?

00:32:09.080 --> 00:32:10.790 align:middle line:84%
We do need divisions
that we can actually

00:32:10.790 --> 00:32:13.160 align:middle line:84%
start to recognize that
we don't have a consensus

00:32:13.160 --> 00:32:15.650 align:middle line:84%
reality, that there are, that
we in order to get at truth,

00:32:15.650 --> 00:32:17.300 align:middle line:84%
you have to sometimes
divide, you have to question,

00:32:17.300 --> 00:32:19.175 align:middle line:84%
you have to challenge,
you have to be at odds

00:32:19.175 --> 00:32:21.650 align:middle line:84%
and polarize in order to
find a new middle ground

00:32:21.650 --> 00:32:22.828 align:middle line:90%
or a new reality?

00:32:22.828 --> 00:32:25.370 align:middle line:84%
>>SEAMAN: Yeah, well, let's look
at what's actually happened.

00:32:25.370 --> 00:32:27.500 align:middle line:84%
The "Washington Post"
is a great example,

00:32:27.500 --> 00:32:30.620 align:middle line:84%
because you had this
brand that people trusted.

00:32:30.620 --> 00:32:32.510 align:middle line:84%
And really, the brand
was trusted because

00:32:32.510 --> 00:32:34.460 align:middle line:84%
of the work of
individuals years ago,

00:32:34.460 --> 00:32:37.100 align:middle line:84%
the former editor in chief,
Katharine Graham I believe

00:32:37.100 --> 00:32:38.240 align:middle line:90%
was not terrible.

00:32:38.240 --> 00:32:40.447 align:middle line:84%
And you go back further,
Woodward and Bernstein.

00:32:40.447 --> 00:32:42.530 align:middle line:84%
That's the reason why
people trust the "Washington

00:32:42.530 --> 00:32:45.650 align:middle line:84%
Post" is that that was the
banner that broke Watergate

00:32:45.650 --> 00:32:46.760 align:middle line:90%
basically.

00:32:46.760 --> 00:32:49.700 align:middle line:84%
And they've been coasting on
that popularity and that trust

00:32:49.700 --> 00:32:52.010 align:middle line:84%
for 30 years and
they've abused it.

00:32:52.010 --> 00:32:55.065 align:middle line:84%
And I think this has happened
in different areas of society,

00:32:55.065 --> 00:32:55.865 align:middle line:90%
not just the media.

00:32:55.865 --> 00:32:56.757 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:32:56.757 --> 00:32:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's right.

